## Implementation

### Changes Made
- `src/burnt/advisor/session.py` - Added `_lookup_job_id_by_name()`, added `job_name` param to `advise()`
- `src/burnt/__init__.py` - Added `job_name` param to public `advise()` function
- `src/burnt/cli/main.py` - Added `--job-name` option
- `tests/unit/test_advisor.py` - Added tests for job name lookup

### Implementation Notes
- Uses `TableRegistry.lakeflow_jobs` for enterprise support
- Case-sensitive exact match: `WHERE job_name = 'name'`
- Error handling: "Job 'name' not found" vs "Multiple jobs match 'name': [list]"
- Mutual exclusivity check happens before any lookup

